00:06:32.419 --> 00:06:36.239
which by and large represent wealthy people,
vastly outnumber the groups representing working

00:06:36.240 --> 00:06:39.820
people, like labor and cooperative groups.
By numbers alone, wealthy interest groups

00:06:39.820 --> 00:06:43.830
would seem to have more power than other groups.
But that's not all. A series of studies that

00:06:43.830 --> 00:06:48.039
culminated in the book Affluence &amp; Influence
by Martin Gilens shows pretty definitively

00:06:48.039 --> 00:06:51.419
that Congress is much more likely to enact
laws that respond to the interests of the

00:06:51.419 --> 00:06:54.919
wealthy, than the poor. It's not that they
never took poor people's interests into account,

00:06:54.919 --> 00:06:58.610
it's just that they are much, much more likely
to make policies that favor the rich. Is that

00:06:58.610 --> 00:07:01.160
the essence of democracy? I think no.

